<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910626-0032</DOCNO><DOCID>910626-0032.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Corning Inc.:   Second-Quarter Net Income   Rose 14% to $75.9 Million</HL><DATE>06/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GLW</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Corning Inc. said second-quarter net income rose 14% to$75.9 million, or 81 cents a share, from $67.1 million, or 71cents a share, a year earlier.   Second-quarter sales rose 15% to $778 million from $678million a year earlier at the Corning, N.Y., company withinterests in glass, specialty materials, telecommunications,and laboratory sciences.</LP><TEXT>   Chairman James R. Houghton said the gains resulted fromstrong performance by the company's fiber optics and cablebusinesses and MetPath Inc.'s clinical laboratory testingservices. &quot;We are pleased that Corning's strategicrepositioning has allowed us to continue moving ahead in theface of a weak economy,&quot; he said.</TEXT></DOC>